articles.headline: Jaden O'Neal gives Florida State highest-rated QB since 2022 class
articles.description: Four-star quarterback Jaden O'Neal, ranked No. 112 in the 2026 ESPN 300, announced his commitment to Florida State on Sunday night, sealing a long-anticipated flip for the former Oklahoma pledge.

articles.headline: Defensive end Richard Wesley commits to Texas Longhorns
articles.description: Defensive end Richard Wesley, a 6-foot-5, 250-pound pass rusher from Chatsworth, California, has committed to Texas, the No. 18 overall prospect in the 2026 ESPN 300 announced on Sunday night following an official visit with the Longhorns this weekend.

articles.headline: Ex-Buckeye Kirk Barton facing charge after fatal crash in Ohio
articles.description: Kirk Barton, a former captain at Ohio State who went on to play in the NFL, faces an aggravated vehicular manslaughter charge following a fatal crash early Saturday morning.

articles.headline: Notre Dame lands commitments from Khary Adams, Joey O'Brien
articles.description: Notre Dame landed pledges from a pair of top 2026 defensive back targets Friday, edging a trio of recruiting rivals to the commitments of No. 8 cornerback Khary Adams and No. 4 athlete prospect Joey O'Brien.

articles.headline: Oklahoma fills need with commitment of 4-star QB Bowe Bentley
articles.description: Four-star quarterback Bowe Bentley, No. 261 in the 2026 ESPN 300, announced his commitment to Oklahoma over LSU on Friday.

article.headline: Addison's late TD gives No. 7 USC 17-14 win over Oregon St
article.description: — Caleb Williams found his favorite target when it mattered most.
article.linkText: Addison's late TD gives No. 7 USC 17-14 win over Oregon St

images.name: USC strikes late on Williams-Addison connection
images.caption: Caleb Williams hits Jordan Addison for a touchdown to put USC back on top.

video.headline: USC strikes late on Williams-Addison connection
video.caption: Caleb Williams hits Jordan Addison for a touchdown to put USC back on top.
video.title: USC strikes late on Williams-Addison connection
video.description: Caleb Williams hits Jordan Addison for a touchdown to put USC back on top.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (USC strikes late on Williams-Addison connection) 2022/09/24

article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- — Caleb Williams found his favorite target when it mattered most. Jordan Addison caught Williams' go-ahead 21-yard touchdown pass with 1:13 left and No. 7 USC overcame a shaky performance for a 17-14 victory against Oregon State on Saturday night. The Beavers, vying to start 4-0 for the first time since 2012, took the lead on Jam Griffin's 18-yard touchdown run with 4:41 remaining. But Williams led an 11-play, 84-yard drive — and even scrambled on a fourth down that preserved it. He connected with Addison for their sixth touchdown of the season. The Trojans (4-0, 2-0 Pac-12) did not look like the team that dominated its first three opponents with 40 or more points per game. Williams threw for a season-low 180 yards. Addison, the 2021 Biletnikoff Award winner who transferred from Pitt, caught three passes for 42 yards. Travis Dye, a transfer from Oregon, caught 19 passes for 136 yards and a score for the Trojans. He never doubted Williams on the final scoring drive. “He was super composed. He was ready to go after it,” Dye said. “He knew that he was going to get it done.” But the Trojans relied on defense most of the night, intercepting Beavers quarterback Chance Nolan four times. “We put ourselves in some really good spots, and we shot ourselves in the foot,” Oregon State offensive lineman Brandon Kipper said. “Against good teams, you're not always going to come back from that.” The Trojans were uncharacteristically sluggish from the start. Oregon State (3-1, 0-1) stopped USC on downs on its opening series. On the second drive, Denis Lynch's 36-yard field goal attempt went wide left. Deshaun Fenwick's 4-yard touchdown run put the Beavers up 7-0 early in the second quarter. It was his fourth TD of the season. Oregon State appeared headed back to the end zone but Nolan was intercepted by Erik Gentry. The Trojans capitalized, going 41 yards on seven plays and finishing with Lynch's 42-yard field goal to narrow it to 7-3 at halftime. Kitan Oladapo sacked Williams on third down for a loss of 11 yards, stalling a USC drive on the Oregon State 45 and forcing a punt. But USC answered. Nolan was intercepted by Ceyair Wright, who ran it back to the Oregon State 26. The Trojans finished the drive with Dye's 7-yard scoring run to put USC in front 10-7. Oregon State was called for a pair of penalties on the ensuing drive and Everett Hayes' 46-yard field goal attempt to tie it with 8:34 to go went right. Oregon State benefited with good field position from USC's punt out of the end zone, and Griffin rushed 18 yards for a touchdown that gave the Beavers back the lead with 4:41 to go. After Addison's touchdown catch, Oregon State's final drive ended with another USC interception. “I’m probably more proud of this win then the previous three,” Trojans coach Lincoln Riley said. "We had to find different ways to win tonight. We got in a slugfest." THE TAKEAWAY USC: The Trojans had scored on their opening drive in the previous three games this season. They had not trailed until Saturday. ... USC's second-half kickoff went out of bounds. Oregon State: The Beavers were without tight end Luke Musgrave, who led the team with 169 yards receiving through the first two games, because of an unspecified injury. There is no timetable for his return. ... Oregon State went to the Coliseum last year and beat the Trojans 45-27. It was the Beavers’ first victory at USC in more than 60 years. TAKEAWAYS With the four interceptions, USC now has 11 on the season. “Each game is its own thing. The previous game doesn’t know if you got turnovers or not. It’s just about the next opportunity," Riley said. "Right now we’re taking advantage of it. We’re playing really hard. We’re active. We’re getting balls tipped up in the air. We’re finishing some of those plays.” UP NEXT USC: The Trojans host Arizona State next Saturday night. Oregon State: The Beavers visit No. 13 Utah next Saturday. ------
